stalteten Natur der Dinge orientieren, wird unter anderem auf der Machtebene offensichtlich. Robert Krajniks Studie zeigt, wie der Subjektbegriff dabei zugespitzter denn je in Umbruch gerät.  aTheatrical-corporeal staging of the self in transition: what impacts does digitisation have on the co-ordination of subject formation?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCulturezGermany. 0aCulture. 0aCyberspace. 0aEducation. 0aIdentity (Philosophical concept). 0aIdentity. 0aTheater. 4aBildung. 4aCyberspace. 4aDigitalisierung. 4aIdentität. 4aKultur. 4aKörper. 4aMedien. 4aMedienpädagogik. 4aMedienästhetik. 4aPädagogik. 4aSubjektbegriff. 4aTheaterwissenschaft. 7aEDUCATION / Research.2bisacsh  aBody.  aConcept of Subject.  aCulture.  aCyberspace.  aDigitalization.  aEducation.  aIdentity.  aMedia Aesthetics.  aMedia Education.  aMedia.  aPedagogy.  aTheatre Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2016z9783110485332oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070101208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839436219zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839436219423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839436219/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-070101-2  PP Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-d